                                          int startYear)
                                   throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                          java.lang.NumberFormatException
        Parses a list of String values into a NaturalDisaster object
        Parameters:
        fields - at least five Strings containing the id, longCountryName, countryIso2, countryIso3, disasterType, numberOfDisastersInThatYear
        startYear - the year of the first event
        Returns:
        a NaturalDisaster object with the provided information
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if less than five Strings are provided
        java.lang.NumberFormatException - if the id or one of the numberOfDisastersInThatYear is not an positive integer
